
@startuml

' Define classes with attributes and relationships

class Song {
  - title: String
  - year: int
  - length: float
  - genre: String
}

class Artist {
  - name: String (PK)
  - dateOfBirth: Date
  - url: String
}

class User {
  - id: String (PK)
  - name: String
  - address: String
}

class BusinessUser {
  - vatNumber: String
}

class RegularUser {
  - hasDownloadedSingles: Set<Song>
  - hasDownloadedAlbums: Set<Album>
  - hasSimilarUsers: Set<RegularUser>
}

class Album {
  - title: String
  - trackList: List<Hit>
}

class Hit {
  - positionInAlbum: int
}

class Single {}

class Upload {
  - uploadDate: Date
}

' Inheritance
User <|-- BusinessUser
User <|-- RegularUser
Song <|-- Single
Song <|-- Hit

' Associations
Artist "1" --> "many" Song : creates
BusinessUser "1" --> "many" Upload : uploads
Upload "1" --> "1" Song : contains
Song "0..1" --> "1" Album : part of (if it's a Hit)
Album "1" --> "many" Hit : includes
RegularUser "many" --> "many" RegularUser : suggestedTo

' Notes
note right of Artist
  An artist is uniquely identified by their name.
end note

note right of Song
  A song can have the same title if from different artists.
  Only (song + artist) combination is unique.
end note

note right of BusinessUser
  Business users can only upload individual songs,
  which are either Singles or Hits.
end note

note right of Album
  Albums consist only of Hits.
  Each hit has a track number in the album.
end note

note right of RegularUser
  Regular users can buy Singles directly or albums.
  They can also be suggested to other regular users.
end note

@enduml

---

### Explanation of Key Elements:

- **`Song`**: Base class for both `Single` and `Hit`. Contains common properties like title, year, etc.
- **`Artist`**: Identified by name; one-to-many relationship with `Song`.
- **`User`**: Abstract base class for `BusinessUser` and `RegularUser`.
- **`BusinessUser`**: Has a VAT number and uploads songs as `Upload`.
- **`RegularUser`**: Can download singles and albums. Also involved in user suggestions.
- **`Album`**: Contains a list of `Hit`s, each with a track number.
- **`Upload`**: Represents the act of uploading a song by a business user.

